#
# Entries here exempt specific files from rule scanning where the rule's
# threat model does not apply. Add a comment with each entry explaining
# WHY the exemption is correct, and pair the exemption with documented
# in-code defensive measures (the rule disable is belt-and-suspenders,
# not a license to skip the actual defense).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# LSP server: filesystem walks of the user's own workspace
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# The `Path Traversal with Actix` (CWE-22) heuristic flags any data flow
# from a `&Path` argument into a `std::fs::*` sink. That rule's threat
# model is HTTP request handlers receiving untrusted client input.
#
# deal-lsp is an LSP server: it runs as the user's own local process,
# inside their editor, against workspace roots their editor chose. There
# is no remote attacker; the user already has full filesystem access to
# the directories the LSP reads. Reading `<workspace_root>/deal.toml`
# and walking `<workspace_root>/**/*.deal` is the LSP's defined contract,
# not a vulnerability.
#
# Defensive measures inside the exempted files (must remain in place):
#   - canonicalize() the workspace root before joining
#   - starts_with() containment check on each resolved path
#   - bounded recursion depth on the workspace walker
#
# Add new LSP filesystem-walking files here explicitly; do NOT broaden
# to lsp/src/** without a security review.
